wiki/Francis_Turretin\" title=\"Francis Turretin\">Francis Turretin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Jonathan_Edwards_(theologian)\" title=\"Jonathan Edwards (theologian)\">Jonathan Edwards</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Charles_Hodge\" title=\"Charles Hodge\">Charles Hodge</a></li></ul></div></div></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame collapsed\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left;background-color:#E0FFFF;;background:#E0FFFF;padding:0.2em;\">Churches</div><div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center;padding-left:0.2em; padding-right:0.2em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Continental_Reformed_church\" title=\"Continental Reformed church\">Continental Reformed</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Presbyterianism\" title=\"Presbyterianism\">Presbyterian</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Congregational_church\" title=\"Congregational church\">Congregationalist</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Reformed_Baptists\" title=\"Reformed Baptists\">Reformed Baptist</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Anglicanism\" title=\"Anglicanism\">Anglican</a></li></ul></div></div></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame collapsed\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left;background-color:#E0FFFF;;background:#E0FFFF;padding:0.2em;\">Peoples</div><div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center;padding-left:0.2em; padding-right:0.2em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Afrikaner_Calvinism\" title=\"Afrikaner Calvinism\">Afrikaners</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Huguenots\" title=\"Huguenots\">Huguenots</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Pilgrims_(Plymouth_Colony)\" title=\"Pilgrims (Plymouth Colony)\">Pilgrims</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Puritans\" title=\"Puritans\">Puritans</a></li>\n<li>other <a href=\"/wiki/English_dissenters\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"English dissenters\">English dissenters</a></li></ul></div></div></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0 0.1em 0.4em\">\n<div class=\"NavFrame collapsed\" style=\"border:none;padding:0\"><div class=\"NavHead\" style=\"font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left;background-color:#E0FFFF;;background:#E0FFFF;padding:0.2em;\">Largest groups</div><div class=\"NavContent\" style=\"font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center;padding-left:0.2em; padding-right:0.2em;\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/World_Communion_of_Reformed_Churches\" title=\"World Communion of Reformed Churches\">World Communion of Reformed Churches</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/World_Reformed_Fellowship\" title=\"World Reformed Fellowship\">World Reformed Fellowship</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/International_Conference_of_Reformed_Churches\" title=\"International Conference of Reformed Churches\">International Conference of Reformed Churches</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/North_American_Presbyterian_and_Reformed_Council\" title=\"North American Presbyterian and Reformed Council\">North American Presbyterian and Reformed Council</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Presbyterianism_in_South_Korea\" title=\"Presbyterianism in South Korea\">Presbyterianism in South Korea</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_Reformed_denominations\" title=\"List of Reformed denominations\">List of Reformed denominations</a></li></ul></div></div></td>\n</tr><tr><td style=\"padding:0.3em 0.4em 0.3em;font-weight:bold;border-top: 1px solid #aaa; border-bottom: 1px solid #aaa;\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/File:Kreuz-hugenotten.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Kreuz-hugenotten.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Kreuz-hugenotten.svg/10px-Kreuz-hugenotten.svg.png\" width=\"10\" height=\"16\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Kreuz-hugenotten.svg/16px-Kreuz-hugenotten.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Kreuz-hugenotten.svg/21px-Kreuz-hugenotten.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"557\" data-file-height=\"849\" /></a> <a href=\"/wiki/Portal:Calvinism\" title=\"Portal:Calvinism\">Calvinism&#32;portal</a></td></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align:right;font-size:115%;padding-top: 0.6em;\"><div class=\"plainlinks hlist navbar mini\"><ul><li class=\"nv-view\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template:Calvinism\" title=\"Template:Calvinism\"><abbr title=\"View this template\">v</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-talk\"><a href=\"/wiki/Template_talk:Calvinism\" title=\"Template talk:Calvinism\"><abbr title=\"Discuss this template\">t</abbr></a></li><li class=\"nv-edit\"><a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:Calvinism&amp;action=edit\"><abbr title=\"Edit this template\">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>In <i>Virtue</i>, Edwards describes his views on the different levels of <a href=\"/wiki/Virtue\" title=\"Virtue\">virtue</a>, specifically \"common <a href=\"/wiki/Morality\" title=\"Morality\">morality</a>\" and \"true (saving) virtue.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Jonathan_Edwards_Center_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Jonathan_Edwards_Center-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> <a href=\"/wiki/God\" title=\"God\">God</a>, Edwards argues, had in mind as the end for his creation of the world His own <a href=\"/wiki/Glory_(religion)\" title=\"Glory (religion)\">glory</a> and not human happiness. Thus, true virtue does not arise from self-love or from any earth-bound selflessness (these were two common views at the time) but from a desire to see God's glory displayed above all. Love of self, family, or nation is good only to the extent that it magnifies the glory of God.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Encyclop\u00e6dia_Britannica_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Encyclop\u00e6dia_Britannica-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History_and_impact\">History and impact</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Nature_of_True_Virtue&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: History and impact\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><i>The Nature of True Virtue</i>, and its companion work, <i>A Dissertation Concerning the End for Which God Created the World</i>, are still popular works today. Modern <a href=\"/wiki/Theologian\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Theologian\">theologian</a> <a href=\"/wiki/John_Piper_(theologian)\" title=\"John Piper (theologian)\">John Piper</a>, who extensively studied the works of Edwards while at <a href=\"/wiki/Seminary\" title=\"Seminary\">Seminary</a>, credits the work with awakening in him \"a deep longing to be a good man.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-John_Piper_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-John_Piper-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Nature_of_True_Virtue&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Jonathan_Edwards_Center-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-Jonathan_Edwards_Center_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-Jonathan_Edwards_Center_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://edwards.yale.edu/research/major-works/nature-of-true-virtue/\">\"The Jonathan Edwards Center at Yale University\"</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-08-27</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=in